---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Fountain Syntax Reference — FountainFormat">
  <main>
    <section class="hero-small">
      <h1>Fountain Syntax Reference</h1>
      <p class="tagline">Everything you need to write screenplays in plain text.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Scene Headings</h2>
        <p>Scene headings (or "slug lines") begin with INT., EXT., EST., INT./EXT., or I/E. followed by a location and time of day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>INT. COFFEE SHOP - DAY

EXT. BEACH - SUNSET

INT./EXT. MOVING CAR - NIGHT</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="note">You can force any line to be a scene heading by starting it with a period: <code>.FLASHBACK</code></p>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Action</h2>
        <p>Action (or "description") is any paragraph that doesn't meet the criteria for another element. Just write normally.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>The door slams open. SARAH storms in, 
soaking wet, mascara running down her face.

She throws her keys on the table.</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="note">Force a line to be action by starting with <code>!</code>: <code>!BANG!</code></p>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Character Names</h2>
        <p>Character names are in ALL CAPS on their own line, with dialogue following below.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>SARAH
I can't believe you did that.

MARCUS (V.O.)
Neither can I.

DETECTIVE #1
Where were you last night?</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="note">Extensions like (V.O.), (O.S.), (CONT'D) go on the same line. Force a character name with <code>@</code>: <code>@McCLANE</code></p>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Dialogue</h2>
        <p>Dialogue is any text following a character name, until the next blank line.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>ANNA
You know what your problem is?
You never listen. Not once.
Not ever.</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Parentheticals</h2>
        <p>Parentheticals (or "wrylies") are wrapped in parentheses on their own line within dialogue.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>MARCUS
(under his breath)
This is insane.
(beat)
Completely insane.</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Dual Dialogue</h2>
        <p>For characters speaking simultaneously, add a caret <code>^</code> before the second character name.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>ANNA
I hate you!

^MARCUS
I love you!</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Transitions</h2>
        <p>Transitions are uppercase lines ending in "TO:" — they appear right-aligned in output.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>CUT TO:

FADE TO BLACK.

DISSOLVE TO:</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="note">Force any line to be a transition with <code>></code>: <code>> FADE OUT.</code></p>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Centered Text</h2>
        <p>Center text by wrapping it with <code>></code> and <code><</code>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>>THE END<

>A Film by Jane Doe<</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Emphasis</h2>
        <p>Style text with asterisks and underscores, like Markdown.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>*italic*
**bold**
***bold italic***
_underline_</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="note">You can combine them: <code>_**bold underline**_</code></p>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Title Page</h2>
        <p>Title page info goes at the very top, as key/value pairs. Blank line ends the title page.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>Title: Big Fish
Credit: Written by
Author: John August
Draft date: 1/20/2003
Contact:
    John August
    john@johnaugust.com</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="note">Common keys: Title, Credit, Author, Source, Draft date, Contact, Copyright</p>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Page Breaks</h2>
        <p>Force a page break with three or more equals signs on their own line.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>===</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Sections & Synopses</h2>
        <p>Organize your script with sections (like Markdown headings) and synopses. These don't appear in printed output.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre># Act 1

## Scene 1

= Sarah meets Marcus at the coffee shop.

INT. COFFEE SHOP - DAY</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="note">Sections use <code>#</code>, synopses use <code>=</code>. Purely for outlining.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Notes</h2>
        <p>Add notes (not printed) with double brackets.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>INT. COFFEE SHOP - DAY [[production: need rain machine]]

SARAH
[[maybe cut this line?]]
I never want to see you again.</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Boneyard</h2>
        <p>Comment out large sections with <code>/* */</code>. Ignored in output.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>/*
INT. DELETED SCENE - DAY

This whole scene was cut.
*/</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="syntax-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Line Breaks</h2>
        <p>Fountain auto-wraps text. Force a line break with two spaces at end of line, or use blank lines.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-label">Fountain</div>
        <pre>MARCUS
I came here to say two things:  
One, I'm sorry.  
Two, goodbye.</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-section">
      <h3>Ready to write?</h3>
      <a href="https://coffeedraft.com" class="cta">Try CoffeeDraft — Free Editor</a>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  main { width: 100%; }

  .hero-small {
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .hero-small h1 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .hero-small .tagline {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .syntax-section {
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-header {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-header p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .example-box {
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .example-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  .example-box pre {
    font-family: 'Courier Prime', Courier, monospace;
    font-size: 12pt;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text);
    padding: 1rem;
    margin: 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .note {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .note code {
    font-family: 'Courier Prime', monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--accent-light);
    background: var(--card);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .cta-section {
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cta {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .cta:hover { background: var(--accent-light); }
</style>